{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":25814,"name":"Alex James","username":"HaeferlKaffee","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/h/71e660/{size}.png","created_at":"2018-09-03T00:14:21.835Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI’m trying to create an effect that requires the world position, or at least position relative to node, of a random vertex on a mesh’s surface\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI’m currently using this:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\t\tGeometry* geom = ((AnimatedModel*)adjNode-\u0026gt;GetComponent\u0026lt;AnimatedModel\u0026gt;())-\u0026gt;GetLodGeometry(0, 0);\n\n\t\tconst unsigned char* vertexData;\n\t\tconst unsigned char* indexData;\n\t\tunsigned vertexSize;\n\t\tunsigned indexSize;\n\t\tconst PODVector\u0026lt;VertexElement\u0026gt;* elements;\n\n\t\tgeom-\u0026gt;GetRawData(vertexData, vertexSize, indexData, indexSize, elements);\n\n\t\t// If data is bad:\n\t\tif (!vertexData || !elements || VertexBuffer::GetElementOffset(*elements, TYPE_VECTOR3, SEM_POSITION) != 0) {\n\t\t\treturn;\n\t\t}\n\t\tconst auto* vertices = (const unsigned char*)vertexData;\n\n\t\t// 16-bit indices ; short\n\t\tif (vertexSize == sizeof(unsigned short)) {\n\t\t\tsurfacePoint = *(Vector3*)(\u0026amp;vertices[(short)Random(0, (int)vertexSize)]);\n\n\t\t\t// Rotate\n\t\t\tsurfacePoint = adjNode-\u0026gt;GetWorldRotation() * surfacePoint;\n\t\t\t// Scale\n\t\t\tsurfacePoint *= adjNode-\u0026gt;GetWorldScale();\n\t\t\t// Position\n\t\t\tsurfacePoint = surfacePoint + adjNode-\u0026gt;GetWorldPosition();\n\n\t\t}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCurrently, the position of the vertex seems to be totally wrong. When I tried to create small spheres at each random location, they would group together at a point not on the mesh, and when enough spheres were created, they didn’t form the mesh they were supposed to be placed upon\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIdeally, it should get the skinned position, i.e. use the animated model not the static mesh\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-09-03T00:16:28.518Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":72,"reads":43,"readers_count":42,"score":368.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":4516,"topic_slug":"getting-the-world-position-of-a-vertex","display_username":"Alex James","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1021,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":25818,"name":"sfrost","username":"SFrost","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/67e7ee/{size}.png","created_at":"2018-09-03T14:07:17.549Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003echange:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003esurfacePoint = *(Vector3*)(\u0026amp;vertices[(short)Random(0, (int)vertexSize)]); \n// Rotate \nsurfacePoint = adjNode-\u0026gt;GetWorldRotation() * surfacePoint; \n// Scale \nsurfacePoint *= adjNode-\u0026gt;GetWorldScale(); \n// Position \nsurfacePoint = surfacePoint + adjNode-\u0026gt;GetWorldPosition();\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eto\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003esurfacePoint = *(Vector3*)(\u0026amp;vertices[(short)Random(0, (int)vertexSize)]); \n\n// local to world\nsurfacePoint = adjNode-\u0026gt;GetWorldTransform() * surfacePoint;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-09-03T14:07:17.549Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":35,"readers_count":34,"score":22.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":4516,"topic_s